{"name":"Ambassador Imperialis","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Whether from serving in the fleet of a Rogue Trader or dealing</p>\n<p>with xenos mercenaries on frontier worlds, the Acolyte is</p>\n<p>experienced in dealing with alien and the most divergent of non-</p>\n<p>Imperial cultures, able to avoid the subtle faux pas that can so</p>\n<p>easily cause a negotiation to deteriorate into bloodshed.</p>\n<p>The character reduces any penalty to Interaction skill tests</p>\n<p>for dealing with xenos or non-Imperial NPCs by 20. In addition,</p>\n<p>once per encounter, he can reroll a failed Interaction skill test when</p>\n<p>interacting with such an NPC.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Fellowship 35, Intelligence 35","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Perception, Social","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"ambassadorimperialis","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"fellowship, investigation","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QtJwjuYGPDe6uVlX"}
{"name":"Archivator","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Whether through years of experience or specialised training, the</p>\n<p>Acolyte is a master of mining information from the Imperium&rsquo;s</p>\n<p>countless archives. From delving into deep info-crypts to searching</p>\n<p>mouldering librarium stacks and deciphering ancient tech-slabs,</p>\n<p>the Acolyte can uncover knowledge thought long lost.</p>\n<p>When making a Scholastic Lore or Forbidden Lore test</p>\n<p>utilising sources of recorded information of any sort, such as</p>\n<p>cogitators, tomes, info-nets, and data-slates, the character can re-</p>\n<p>roll a failed test once with a &ndash;10 penalty. In addition, tests to</p>\n<p>perform research or find information in these circumstances take</p>\n<p>half the usual time.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Int 40","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Knowledge, Perception","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"archivator","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"knowledge","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Y84AWtWpuCyA2FG6"}
{"name":"Field Vivisection","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The Acolyte is well-versed in the blasphemous anatomy of his</p>\n<p>xenos foes, and uses this knowledge to utmost effect, both in the</p>\n<p>laboratorium and on the battlefield.</p>\n<p>Each time this talent is taken, the character selects the</p>\n<p>Specialisation that matches the Characteristic and Aptitude pair</p>\n<p>(Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill) used in purchase. When using the</p>\n<p>Called Shot action with a melee or ranged attack (depending on</p>\n<p>the Specialisation) against a target for which the character has the</p>\n<p>appropriate Forbidden Lore (Xenos) skill, he makes a Medicae</p>\n<p>(WS) or Medicae (BS) test in place of the normal Weapon Skill</p>\n<p>or Ballistic Skill test.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill 40, Forbidden Lore (Xenos–Any), Rank 2 in the Medicae skill","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill, Knowledge","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"Ranged, Melee","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"fieldvivisection","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"range, melee","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BlKcc04ujIwrMx3W"}
{"name":"Grenadier","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The Acolyte knows that grenades and other explosives are amongst</p>\n<p>the most effective ways to bring down marauding alien beasts, or</p>\n<p>to quickly thin out hordes of lesser xenos monstrosities.</p>\n<p>When the character misses with a thrown weapon or weapon</p>\n<p>with the Blast quality, he may reduce the distance it scatters by a</p>\n<p>number of metres up to half his BS bonus.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Ballistic Skill 35","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Ballistic Skill, Finesse","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"grenadier","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"range","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qtjAG0XD430UK2Xq"}
{"name":"Hotshot Pilot","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>When the situation calls for it, the opeator stretches the bounds</p>\n<p>of his abilities, displaying impressive feats of manoeuvring. This</p>\n<p>experience has also taught the Acolyte how to recover from what</p>\n<p>might become fatal mishaps for a less skilled operator attempting</p>\n<p>such manoeuvres.</p>\n<p>When the Acolyte succeeds on an Operate test (or Survival</p>\n<p>test in the case of a living steed), he may voluntarily suffer 1 level</p>\n<p>of Fatigue to add a number of degrees of success equal to half</p>\n<p>of his Agility bonus. When the Acolyte fails an Operate test (or</p>\n<p>Survival test in the case of a living steed), he may voluntarily suffer</p>\n<p>1 level of Fatigue in order to reduce the degrees of failure by an</p>\n<p>amount equal to his Agility bonus, to a minimum of 1.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Rank 2 in Survival or any Operate skill, Agility 35","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Agility, Tech","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"hotshotpilot","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"pilot","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"RPhrmOi3IfbXfmxA"}
{"name":"Hull Down","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The Acolyte remains aware of his foes at all times in combat,</p>\n<p>carefully angling his vehicle or steed at each moment to present</p>\n<p>a narrower silhouette to all attackers, as well as taking the best</p>\n<p>advantage of any intervening terrain to gain cover.</p>\n<p>When the character takes a vehicle combat action with the</p>\n<p>Movement subtype, his vehicle or steed counts the value of its Size</p>\n<p>trait as being one lower for purposes of attack modifiers and the</p>\n<p>benefits of cover until the start of his next turn.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"3","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Rank 2 in Survival or any Operate skill","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Agility, Fieldcraft","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"hulldown","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"pilot","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"UjsnVbisZAyhcyKD"}
{"name":"Leaping Dodge","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The Acolyte has become practiced at escaping weapons</p>\n<p>that cover an area to deadly effect, from flamers to strange</p>\n<p>xenos devices. When he would make an Agility test to avoid</p>\n<p>attacks from weapons with the Spray quality, he may make the</p>\n<p>test using his Dodge (Ag) skill instead.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Agility 35, Rank 2 in the Dodge skill","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Agility, Defence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"leapingdodge","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"defence, dodge","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6Dp9jwRiRsws0P3O"}
{"name":"Lexographer","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>From years poring over dusty tomes and examining ancient</p>\n<p>ruins on forgotten worlds&mdash;and perhaps even speaking face-to-</p>\n<p>face with inhuman beings&mdash;the Acolyte has become an expert in</p>\n<p>deciphering lost human languages as well as those of xenos.</p>\n<p>The character can attempt any Linguistics skill in which</p>\n<p>he is not trained as an untrained skill test as if it were not a</p>\n<p>Specialist skill.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Rank 3 in Linguistics (Any)","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Intelligence, Knowledge","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"lexographer","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"knowledge, research","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Np0N7Z7WuysXEkwF"}
{"name":"Push the Limit","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Whether through study, practice, or sheer intuition, the Acolyte</p>\n<p>is aware of the limits of his vehicle or steed, and knows how to</p>\n<p>push it to those limits and beyond. Although overtaxing a beast</p>\n<p>or executing wheel-tearing turns can provide a great advantage in</p>\n<p>combat or pursuit, a single wrong move can prove catastrophic,</p>\n<p>injuring the pilot or even ripping his vehicle apart.</p>\n<p>Once per round, the character may add +20 to an Operate</p>\n<p>test (or Survival test in the case of living steeds); however, if he</p>\n<p>fails the test by 4 or more degrees of failure, immediately roll 1d5</p>\n<p>on Table 7&ndash;32: Motive Systems Critical Hit Effects on page 257</p>\n<p>of the D ark h ErEsy Core Rulebook and apply the result. If he</p>\n<p>is riding a living mount, roll 1d5 on Table 7&ndash;18: Impact Critical</p>\n<p>Effects &ndash; Leg on page 239 of the D ark h ErEsy Core Rulebook</p>\n<p>and apply the result.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"3","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Rank 2 in Survival or any Operate skill, Tech-Use","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Perception, Tech","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"pushthelimit","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"pilot, tech","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"VqQePW8jtqoWwNWe"}
{"name":"Skilled Rider","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Often, the best way to overcome the heretic is with merciless speed,</p>\n<p>and so many Acolytes make extensive use of vehicles and mounts</p>\n<p>in their pursuit of humanity&rsquo;s enemies. Whether the character has</p>\n<p>used his prized bike until it feels like an extension of his own body,</p>\n<p>or he has the experience necessary to instantly adjust to the strange</p>\n<p>mounts and vehicles found across the Askellon Sector, moving to</p>\n<p>or from the saddle or pilot&rsquo;s seat is second nature.</p>\n<p>Whenever the character would be thrown from or tossed</p>\n<p>about within his vehicle, he makes an Ordinary (+10) Agility test.</p>\n<p>If he succeeds, the character may choose to either land safely</p>\n<p>on his feet or retain in his original position in the vehicle. In</p>\n<p>addition, once per round the character can attempt an Ordinary</p>\n<p>(+10) Agility test to Mount or Dismount a vehicle as a Free Action.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Rank 2 in any Operate skill","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Agility, Fieldcraft","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"skilledrider","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"pilot","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"FmWs0fIICSmJY0fA"}
{"name":"Weapon Intuition","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>In the prosecution of his duties against the alien, the Acolyte</p>\n<p>wields the most arcane and rare weapons the Adeptus Mechanicus</p>\n<p>can craft, and perhaps even takes up the very armaments of the</p>\n<p>xenos to better combat it. From years of experience, the character</p>\n<p>can quickly discern the firing mechanisms and balance of even the</p>\n<p>strangest weapons, regardless of its origin.</p>\n<p>The character reduces the penalty for using a weapon without</p>\n<p>the proper training by 10.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"3","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Exotic Weapon Training (Any)","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Intelligence, Finesse","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"weaponintuition","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"combat","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GQfU0CJE02Du7dM1"}
{"name":"Xenosavant","permission":{"default":0,"NDY0P4qfBmJvZ9SS":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>In his study and prosecution of the xenos threat, the Acolyte has</p>\n<p>become well-versed in the ways and forms of the myriad alien</p>\n<p>races that menace humanity.</p>\n<p>The character can attempt any Forbidden Lore (Xenos) test</p>\n<p>in which he is not trained as an untrained skill test as if it were not</p>\n<p>a Specialist skill.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Rank 3 in Forbidden Lore (Xenos–Any)","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Intelligence, Knowledge","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"xenosavant","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"knowledge, investigation","type":"String"}},"flags":{"specials":{}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0Dxu1IpkaHvEacT3"}
